		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Henri Cartier-Bresson</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div style="float:right;width:315px;">
<table class="infobox biography vcard vevent" cellspacing="5" style="width: 22em; text-align: left; font-size: 88%; line-height: 1.5em; width:22em; font-size:95%; text-align:left;">
<tr>
<td colspan="2" class="fn summary" style="text-align:center; font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; text-align:center; font-size:125%;"><b>Henri Cartier-Bresson</b></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="padding:0.2em 1.0em 0.2em 0.2em; background:transparent; line-height:1.2em; text-align:left; font-size:90%;">Born</th>
<td class="" style="padding:0.2em; line-height:1.3em; vertical-align:middle; font-size:90%;">August 22, 1908<span style="display:none">(<span class="bday">1908-08-22</span>)</span><br />
<a href="/wiki/Chanteloup-en-Brie" title="Chanteloup-en-Brie">Chanteloup-en-Brie</a>, <a href="/wiki/France" title="France">France</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="padding:0.2em 1.0em 0.2em 0.2em; background:transparent; line-height:1.2em; text-align:left; font-size:90%;">Died</th>
<td class="" style="padding:0.2em; line-height:1.3em; vertical-align:middle; font-size:90%;">August 3, 2004 (aged&#160;95)<br />
<a href="/wiki/Montjustin" title="Montjustin">Montjustin</a>, <a href="/wiki/France" title="France">France</a></td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
<p><b>Henri Cartier-Bresson</b> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1908-08-22"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="08-22"><a href="/wiki/August_22" title="August 22">August 22</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1908" title="1908">1908</a></span> – <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2004-08-03"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="08-03"><a href="/wiki/August_3" title="August 3">August 3</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2004" title="2004">2004</a></span>) was a <a href="/wiki/France" title="France">French</a> <a href="/wiki/Photography" title="Photography">photographer</a> considered to be the father of modern <a href="/wiki/Photojournalism" title="Photojournalism">photojournalism</a>, an early adopter of <a href="/wiki/35_mm" title="35 mm" class="mw-redirect">35 mm</a> format, and the master of candid photography. He helped develop the "<a href="/wiki/Street_photography" title="Street photography">street photography</a>" style that has influenced generations of photographers that followed.</p>
